Then, `eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ` would be the infimum of all `C` such that `f(x) ≤ C` for `μ`-a.e. `x`. Since `f` is essentially bounded by `C`, we have `eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ ≤ C < ⊤`.

